p.b: Increased glycolytic flux as an outcome of whole-genome duplication in yeast.
p.em: GC Conant and KH Wolfe, Mol Syst Biol 3:129,2007

body.p: This is the original model reproducing figure 3A of the article submitted by the authors. There exists a curated version with BIOMD0000000176 that reproduces figures 2A,3A and 3B from the publication. BIOMD0000000176 encompasses MODEL2426780967, MODEL2427021978, MODEL2427095802.

note.value: Model used by Conant and Wolfe, 2007, unpublished. Taken from Pritchard and Kell, 2002, Eur J Biochem 269: 3894-3904.

Results for the analysis in the above manuscript (Figure 3A) were obtained by manually changing the value of Vmax for the ten reactions of glycolysis (including HXT but excluding TPI) to 0.9*Vmax, where Vmax is the value for the reaction in this file
